      "source_region": "div.problem-additional-text",
      "text": "A question of Erd\\H{o}s reported in problem B15 of Guy's collection \\cite{Gu04}."
    },
    "statement": {
      "sha256": "811ff8f8695990d76b6bd9d24ab4f1abc76b3e04827b41524c29a4c9c2025f48",
      "source_region": "div#content",
      "text": "How many solutions are there to\\[\\sigma(a)+\\sigma(b)=\\sigma(a+b)\\]with $a+b\\leq x$, where $\\sigma$ is the sum of divisors function? Is it $\\sim cx$ for some constant $c>0$?"
    }
